decision_conditions:
No development above ground level shall take place in the relevant part of the development until a detailed access statement has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  The statement shall include:
(a) details of means of access and egress of buildings, including details of entry systems;
(b) way-finding systems (signage);
(c) locations of and details of the lifts and forecourts to the lifts, including their sizes and specifications;
(d) details of the wheelchair accessible residential units, including locations, floor plans and specifications of the interior;
(e) details of the Lifetime Homes Standards specifications to be implemented;
(f) details of access to bin storage and any post boxes where applicable;
(g) details of colour and contrast of fixtures and fittings, and colour and contrast of signage.

The development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details and implemented prior to occupation of the development. 

Reason: To ensure an inclusive environment in accordance with Policy CP3 of the Core Strategy (July 2010) and Policy BP11 of the Borough Wide Development Policies DPD (March 2011).

No development shall take place in the relevant part of the development until a Construction and Environmental Management Plan (CEMP) and a Site Waste Management Plan (SWMP) has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The Plans shall provide details of all methods of site preparation and construction of the development and include:

a.	traffic management (including a Construction Logistics Plan); 
b.	demolition and clearance (including security hoardings);
c.	site remediation and ground works;
d.	waste management and methods to minimise waste; 
e.	surface water pollution control;
f.	location and type of stored materials;
g.	dust, smoke and odour control;
h.	avoidance of fires;
i.	wheel washing;
j.	noise and vibration;
k.	hours of operation; No demolition, construction or building works shall be carried out other than internal works not audible outside the site boundary except between the hours of 08:00 to 18:00 Monday to Friday and 08:00 to 13:00 Saturday or at any time on Bank or Public holidays without the prior written approval of the Local Planning Authority, unless the works have been approved in advance under section 61 of the Control of Pollution Act 1974. 
l.	details of a nominated Developer/Resident Liaison Representative with an address and contact telephone number to be circulated to those residents consulted on the application by the developer's representatives. This person will act as first point of contact for residents who have any problems or questions related to the ongoing development;
m.	implementation and monitoring.  

Demolition and construction work and associated activities are to be carried out in accordance with the recommendations contained within British Standard 5228:2009, "Code of practice for noise and vibration control on construction and open sites". Parts 1 and 2.  The approved Plans shall be implemented for the entire period of the works at the site.

Reason: In the interest of pollution and residential amenity, in accordance with Policy BP8 of the Borough Development Policies DPD (March 2011).
